reviewText: A friend recommended the movie A WALK IN THE CLOUDS.  It was okay but not gripping nor particularly touching.  I would not recommend it to others.The second feature, A GOOD YEAR, was good in name only....didn't finish watching it.

reviewText: but, they are not supposed to be,very enjoyable, .. i have read that the book 'a good year', has plot twists, and that in comparison, this movie is disappointing, .. well, i have never read the book, i enjoyed crowe's acting and development, reflections, he made the movie quite believableand, who does not love cutie-boy keanu reeves, ... yes, this is not earth-shaking, but he delivers a solid performance, & wow, anthony quinn!, what a voice, makes me want to watch all of his old movies, .. maybe i should subscribe to one of the on-line movie packages!,all in all, ... cannot see anyone being disappointed with these two movies, .. and two, for such a price!,

reviewText: Both of these movies for 1 low price. I just love both of these movies. They are very romantic, but not sickening or explicit. The plots and cast actors are the best. Buy these movies, you'll love them. They might be chick flicks, but the male charactors are not wimpy (Russell Crowe?). Keanu Reeves on "A Walk On The Cloud" is a "nice guy", but again, not a wimp. I love "A Good Year" because it had a lot of humor. Anyway, get them. You won't be sorry!
